  "prompt": "Can you confirm if money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, **money laundering is illegal** in virtually every country around the world. Money laundering is the process of disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, often by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions, to make it appear legitimate.\n\n### Key Points:  \n- **Definition**: It involves concealing the source of funds obtained through illegal activities, such as drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or organized crime.  \n- **Legality**: Money laundering is a criminal offense under international and national laws. Most countries have specific **anti-money laundering (AML) laws** and regulations to combat it.  \n- **Punishments**: Penalties for money laundering can include substantial fines, imprisonment, and asset forfeiture.  \n- **Global Efforts**: Organizations like the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)** work to set international standards for combating money laundering and terrorist financing.  \n\nIf you have further questions or need more details, feel free to ask!",
